{
  "marker": "frontend-only: pending backend",
  "description": "Frontend-implementation metadata for the forward-contract operations declared in packages/types/openapi.json with x-backend-status. The canonical spec owns paths/methods/schemas; this registry records which typed function and module implements each op, its surfaces, and msw_implemented (an MSW handler answers it). Every op carries backend_status — MISSING (no backend equivalent), PARTIAL (backend substrate exists but no usable API), DRIFT (overlaps or conflicts with an existing contract op; reconcile with the backend), FUTURE-AUTH (spec-target auth provider journey beyond the demo backend). body_extensions declare extra fields the frontend sends on real contract ops (folded into the canonical schemas as optional properties); they are backend asks, not silent drift. scripts/verify-data-layer.mjs asserts spec-registry parity both ways plus handler coverage; the registry also feeds the endpoint checklist.",
